- Read .ralph/current_task.txt -> .ralph/tasks/story-secure-explicit-node-config/03-task-enforce-role-specific-credential-usage-across-runtime.md.
- Reviewed task plan marked TO BE VERIFIED; ran deep skeptical verification with 4 explorer subagents.
- Confirmed current bug: runtime startup + HA rewind inherit user/dbname from ProcessDispatchDefaults::contract_stub() (user=postgres) because process_defaults_from_config only overwrites host/port; clone/basebackup and rewind both use that same stub-derived conninfo.
- Found additional critical pitfalls:
  - many RuntimeConfig fixtures drift (rewind_conn_identity.user=postgres while roles.rewinder.username=rewinder) so new cross-field validation will require updating a long list of fixtures;
  - process layer has no env injection so RoleAuthConfig::Password cannot be used; also PgRewindSpec lacks validation for source_conninfo fields;
  - e2e harness/real tests assume psql -U postgres and do not provision replicator role on the primary; if basebackup switches to replicator user, tests need harness provisioning.
- Updated the task plan in .ralph/tasks/story-secure-explicit-node-config/03-task-enforce-role-specific-credential-usage-across-runtime.md:
  - added explicit note that roles must exist on source server;
  - added secret-safety requirement (do not store cleartext secrets in Debug structs; keep SecretSource until spawn);
  - expanded exhaustive file checklist of fixtures to update;
  - added e2e harness steps (psql user/db not hardcoded; ensure replicator role exists).
- Replaced the plan terminator from TO BE VERIFIED to NOW EXECUTE.
- Next: execute the plan exactly as written (no further exploration), then run make check/test/test-long/lint until 100% green.
